        "number": 6018,
        "title": "fix(router-core): correct TypeScript param inference for routes nested inside _pathless directories (#6011)",
        "user": {
          "login": "devel-maverick",
          "id": 214442331,
          "node_id": "U_kgDODMghWw",
          "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/214442331?v=4",
          "gravatar_id": "",
          "url": "https://api.github.com/users/devel-maverick",
          "html_url": "https://github.com/devel-maverick",
          "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/devel-maverick/followers",
          "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/devel-maverick/following{/other_user}",
          "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/devel-maverick/gists{/gist_id}",
          "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/devel-maverick/starred{/owner}{/repo}",
          "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/devel-maverick/subscriptions",
          "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/devel-maverick/orgs",
          "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/devel-maverick/repos",
          "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/devel-maverick/events{/privacy}",
          "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/devel-maverick/received_events",
          "type": "User",
          "user_view_type": "public",
          "site_admin": false
        },
        "labels": [
          {
            "id": 8091825165,
            "node_id": "LA_kwDOCd_tpc8AAAAB4k90DQ",
            "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/TanStack/router/labels/package:%20router-core",
            "name": "package: router-core",
            "color": "FEF7ED",
            "default": false,
            "description": ""
          }
        ],
        "state": "open",
        "locked": false,
        "assignees": [],
        "milestone": null,
        "comments": 5,
        "created_at": "2025-12-03T16:39:55Z",
        "updated_at": "2026-02-13T23:34:33Z",
        "closed_at": null,
        "assignee": null,
        "author_association": "NONE",
        "issue_field_values": [],
        "type": null,
        "active_lock_reason": null,
        "draft": false,
        "pull_request": {
          "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/TanStack/router/pulls/6018",
          "html_url": "https://github.com/TanStack/router/pull/6018",
          "diff_url": "https://github.com/TanStack/router/pull/6018.diff",
          "patch_url": "https://github.com/TanStack/router/pull/6018.patch",
          "merged_at": null
        },
        "body": "**Description**\r\n\r\nThis PR fixes a TypeScript inference issue where route parameters are not detected when a route file is placed inside a _pathless directory. Runtime behavior was already correct, but TypeScript always inferred router.matchRoute() as false, causing parameter access to fail at compile time.\r\n\r\n**Problem**\r\n\r\nWhen using a structure like:\r\n\r\n`routes/_pathless/nested/$id.tsx`\r\n\r\n\r\nthe type-level path becomes:\r\n\r\n`\"/_pathless/nested/$id\"`\r\n\r\n\r\nEven though _pathless is removed from the actual URL at runtime, the type system still sees it as a real segment. This prevents $id from being extracted, producing:\r\n\r\n```\r\nconst match = router.matchRoute({ \r\n  to: \"/nested/$id\", \r\n  params: { id: \"123\" } \r\n})\r\n\r\n// match inferred as false only\r\nmatch?.id // Property 'id' does not exist\r\n```\r\n\r\n **Fix**\r\n\r\nWe normalize the type-level path by stripping _pathless before param extraction:\r\n\r\n`StripPathless<TFrom>, StripPathless<TTo>`\r\n\r\n\r\nThen apply this normalization inside ValidateParams:\r\n\r\n```\r\nexport type ValidateParams<\r\n  TRouter extends AnyRouter = RegisteredRouter,\r\n  TTo extends string | undefined = undefined,\r\n  TFrom extends string = string,\r\n> = PathParamOptions<\r\n  TRouter,\r\n  StripPathless<TFrom>,\r\n  TTo extends string ? StripPathless<TTo> : TTo\r\n>\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis ensures TypeScript sees the correct path:\r\n\r\n`\"/nested/$id\"`\r\n\r\n\r\nallowing parameter extraction to work as intended.\r\n\r\n **Result (after fix)**\r\n```\r\nconst match = router.matchRoute({\r\n  to: \"/nested/$id\",\r\n  params: { id: \"123\" }\r\n})\r\n\r\n// ✔ match: false | { id: string }\r\nmatch?.id // correctly typed\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nfixes: (#6011)\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n* **Improvements**\n  * Path validation in the router now features automatic normalization of special routing segments for consistent and reliable behavior. This enhancement reduces configuration edge cases, improves routing predictability, and ensures stable handling across complex scenarios with multiple parameters and nested paths, making the routing system more robust and maintainable.\n\n<sub>✏️ Tip: You can customize this high-level summary in your review settings.</sub>\n\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
